1. Download a copy of Arch Linux for Arm Processors
2. dd bs=1M if=arch_arm.img of=/dev/sdX (where sdX is the SD card)
3. Use parted or gparted to expand the filesystem on the SD card to fill the space
4. Login to the pi: It's initial address is alarmpi
   -- ssh root@alarmpi #password is root
5. pacman -Syu #update the system
6. passwd #Change the root user password
7. adduser -m -g <group> -s <shell> <username>  # Install any shells you want before this
8. pacman -S sudo vim emacs git
9. Setup user environment (.bashrc, aliases, etc)
10. edit /etc/hostname
-- Setup the wifi
11. install hostapd fakeroot binutils patch make gcc
12. wget and install https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/ud/udhcp/udhcp.tar.gz
12. edit /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf # ssid, wpa_passphrase
13. systemctl enable hostapd.service # Start it too
14. edit /etc/udhcpd.conf
    start 192.168.7.2
    end 192.168.7.254
    interface wlan0
    remaining yes
    opt dns 8.8.8.8 4.2.2.2
    opt subnet 255.255.255.0
    opt router 192.168.7.1
    opt lease 864000
15. edit /etc/conf.d/network@wlan0
    address=192.168.7.1
    netmask=24
    broadcast=192.168.7.255
16. Add systemd unit file -- give here
17. systemctl enable network@wlan0.service # and start    
**18. fix /usr/lib/systemd/system/udhcpd.service (/usr/sbin to /usr/bin) ... not working?

** Okay, nvm with udhcpd, switching to dhcpd
19. Install dhcpd
20. edit /etc/dhcpd.conf
